This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for Wasm lowering.

## Core concept

Wasm lowering translates selected validated HIR through a structured backend-owned lower IR and explicit ABI or layout plans.

## Beanstalk boundary

The final mixed HTML design uses:

- JavaScript-owned `start`
- entry-specific function partitioning
- backwards propagation of JavaScript requirements
- no Wasm-to-JavaScript Beanstalk call
- generated JavaScript-to-Wasm wrappers
- one page-local runtime and shared memory
- imported runtime memory for linked Wasm variants
- structured Wasm LIR
- central output writing

The final design removes dispatcher loops, `bst_start`, per-module memory, helper booleans and the `i64` Int bridge.

## Rewrite focus

Explain structured control flow, ABI design, linear memory, shared runtime ownership and the boundary between a core target backend and HTML project orchestration.

Canonical details live in `docs/build-system-design.md`.
